statement.p:
Which of the following expressions are integers? Which are rational? Which are both? Which are undefined? Explain.


\displaystyle \frac{120}{-12}

\displaystyle \frac{120}{-12}

\displaystyle \frac{12\times 0}{-12}

\displaystyle \frac{12}{-120}

\displaystyle \frac{10}{5-5}

\displaystyle \frac{10}{-5-5}

\displaystyle \sqrt{100}

\displaystyle \sqrt{10}

\displaystyle 10.9999


\displaystyle 10.\overline{9}

We know that \pi is irrational. Which of the following are also irrational? Support your reasoning.


\displaystyle \frac{\pi}{2\pi}

\displaystyle \frac{1}{2\pi}

\displaystyle \frac{3+\pi}{2\pi}

\displaystyle \frac{3\pi+\pi}{2\pi}

\displaystyle 3.\overline{1459}
